Package: pakhom
Title: AI-Integrated Thematic Analysis Following Braun and Clarke
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person(given = c("Abanoub", "J."), family = "Armanious",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "armaniousabanoub@gmail.com")
Description: Conducts AI-assisted reflexive thematic analysis (Braun & Clarke,
    2006) on online discussion forum data using OpenAI or Anthropic APIs. Features
    codebook-first learning from previous manual analyses, progressive sequential
    coding (one entry at a time), embedding-augmented iterative bottom-up theme
    emergence with co-occurrence context, deterministic code-path theme assignment,
    triangulated thematic saturation detection, and inter-model reliability via
    cross-run comparison. Supports checkpoint/resume, mid-pipeline researcher
    review (CSV or QDPX format), QDPX export for QDA software interoperability,
    AI decision audit trails (JSONL), within-run longitudinal analysis, and
    publication-quality HTML reports. The package name 'pakhom' (Coptic for
    'eagle') honors Saint Pachomius the Great (c. 292-348 CE), whose written
    Rule of communal discipline established the genre of methodology-as-written-
    document, of which this package is a digital descendant. Development
    assisted by Claude (Anthropic).
